# Ancient Indian mathematics, applied to SPhotonix — verified

Two algorithms from the Indian mathematical tradition, held to the project
standard (every claim has a test; run the files).

## 1. Aryabhata’s kuttaka (Aryabhatiya, c. 499 CE) → carry-free accumulator

**Project problem touched:** the PE’s 32-bit accumulator is the widest carry
chain in design.sv — a real critical-path limiter.

**What was built & proven (`ancient_kernels.py`, 6/6 PASS):**

- kuttaka (extended Euclid / “pulverizer”): identity verified, 5000 pairs
- CRT reconstruction via kuttaka constants: EXHAUSTIVE round-trip, all 9009
  ints for moduli {7,9,11,13}
- RNS over {251,253,255,256}: M = 4,145,475,840; proven exact for any int8
  dot product of length ≤ 126,509
- RNS MAC == exact MAC, exhaustive over all 65,536 int8 pairs
- RNS dot == int64 dot, lengths up to 100,000
- every channel value < 256 → 8-bit datapaths suffice

**Then wired into the array (`rns_systolic.py`):** register-for-register
mirror of the proven golden model — same skew/de-skew/valid pipe/two-phase
commit, LATENCY=7 — with the int32 partial-sum registers replaced by four
≤8-bit residue channels and ONE CRT decoder at the array edge.

- RNS array == golden array == A@W: 300 random trials, **0 mismatches**
- per-cycle width audit: largest residue register ever observed = 255 < 256

**Honest cost ledger:** RNS wins carry DEPTH (clock-speed lever), loses AREA
(~4× multipliers). Decode sits off the hot path. This matches the published
tradeoff (RNS-TPU patents US 10,599,398 / US 10,387,122; kuttaka-based CRT:
Rao & Yang 2006, “Aryabhata Remainder Theorem”; RNS accelerators reaching
FP32-class accuracy with ~6-bit channels: arXiv 2306.09481). A lever, not magic.

## 2. Bakhshali square root (~3rd–7th c. CE) → quantvec normalization

One Bakhshali step is QUARTIC (measured order ≈ 4.5–6 vs Newton’s ≈ 2.2–2.7
in our test): correct digits roughly quadruple per step. Relevant wherever
quantvec normalizes vectors. Verified empirically in `ancient_kernels.py`.

## What ancient mathematics does NOT solve

- The pending EDA Playground run of design.sv/testbench.sv (only you can do that)
- IVF recall collapse on isotropic data (property of the method, not a bug)
- A future `design_rns.sv` would itself need the same simulator gate

Next hardware step if pursued: write design_rns.sv (8-bit modular MAC PEs +
edge CRT decoder) — but only AFTER the existing design.sv passes a real tool.
